#conventions #dev

> TDD, self-hosting, and commit conventions for this project.

Development conventions for this project.

TDD — write a failing test that captures the assumption first, then write code.
Tests are grouped into classes by method/feature (e.g. TestParseTags, TestUpsertNote).
Use tmp_path for file isolation. store + memo_dir fixtures in test_store.py are canonical.

Self-hosting — use eshp itself during development to record decisions and context.
The eshp/ folder in this repo IS the project memory graph.

Commit convention — EshpStore does not auto-commit.
Always call store.conn.commit() after mutations.
Always call store.close() when done.

Slugs — kebab-case filenames without the .eshp extension. path.stem everywhere.

Tags — no # prefix in DB or EshpNote.tags. Only present in raw file text.

